    • Field Detail

      • COMPARATOR

        public static final Comparator<CaseClass> COMPARATOR
        This comparator orders the arguments lexicographically. That is, the arguments are ordered according to the first value, and if they're equal then the second value, and so on. The values must be an instance of Comparable or CaseClass (in which case the comparator is applied recursively). A ClassCastException is thrown if one of the values is neither of these, or if the sequences of names do not match exactly.

      • equals

        public static boolean equals(CaseClass o1,
                             Object o2)
        Compare the arguments for equality. Return true if and only if the arguments have compatible types (see below) and they consist of equal sequences of names and values, in the same order.

        By default the types of the arguments are compatible if and only if they are equal, i.e. o1.getClass() == o2.getClass(). However if both arguments implement FlexiblyEqual, then the types are compatible if each is a subtype of the class returned by the other's FlexiblyEqual.equalsBaseClass(). This is analogous to a traditional implementation of equals using an instanceof check.

        Use this along with hashCode(CaseClass).
